The paper deals with the problem of approximating the number of k-cliques in an undirected graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields. The paper proposes an algorithm that parameterizes the complexity in terms of graph arboricity, which is a measure of graph density. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to subfields of computer science that deal with graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization, such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
